Japan's Itochu Corp. said Thursday its pre-tax  profits plunged 38.3 percent from a year earlier to 30.8 billion yen (299  million dollars) in the year to March.
Itochu, a major trading house, said its sales declined 12.9 percent to  16.1 trillion yen in the same period.
The company has forecast an improved pre-tax profit of 36 billion yen in  the current year despite a slightly lower sales projection of 16 trillion yen.
